<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 13 at 5:14AM CST  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...Slick Travel Conditions...
Light snow will continue to move across the area over the next few
hours, eventually tapering off from north to south by mid morning.
Total accumulations will be light, and generally a dusting to
under an inch. However, with cold temperatures in the single
digits and teens, accumulation will occur on untreated roadways,
bridges and sidewalks leading to slippery travel conditions.
If you will be traveling early this morning, be sure to slow down
and give yourself extra time to reach your destination.</description>
